## Task Summary: Hook fail-closed Rust dispatcher with thin Python launchers

**Track:** hook-fail-closed-2026-03-11
**Task:** ERR-06 fix — migrate security-critical hooks to Rust fail-closed design
**Date:** 2026-03-11

### Changes

- libs/domain/src/decision.rs: shared Decision enum (SRP, used by guard and hook)
- libs/domain/src/hook/: HookName, HookContext, HookInput, HookVerdict, HookError types
- libs/domain/src/guard/verdict.rs: migrated GuardVerdict to shared Decision
- libs/usecase/src/hook.rs: HookHandler trait (OCP), Guard/LockAcquire/LockRelease handlers, resolve_lock_mode
- apps/cli/src/commands/hook.rs: HookCommand dispatch, stdin JSON parsing, exit code mapping
- .claude/hooks/block-direct-git-ops.py: thin launcher for sotp hook dispatch
- .claude/hooks/file-lock-acquire.py: thin launcher with no cwd fallback
- .claude/hooks/file-lock-release.py: thin launcher (PostToolUse, cannot block)
- .claude/hooks/_shared.py: warn_and_log advisory hook helper
- scripts/verify_orchestra_guardrails.py: marker updated for os._exit(2)

### Why

Python hooks had fail-open exception handling (ERR-06). Security-critical hooks now
delegate to Rust `sotp hook dispatch` where the type system and Result type structurally
guarantee fail-closed behavior. 3-round Codex review converged to zero findings.
